snippet: The meager expectations of Hamdeen Sabahi, who is opposing the former general Abdul-Fattah el-Sisi in the race for Egypt’s presidency, illustrate the breakdown of Egypt’s political life since the presidential election two years ago.
abstract: Egyptian presidential candidate Hamdeen Sabahi says he does not really expect a fair race against his opponent Abdel Fattah el-Sisi, former military officer who led takeover of elected government.
lead_paragraph: The meager expectations of Hamdeen Sabahi, who is opposing the former general Abdul-Fattah el-Sisi in the race for Egypt’s presidency, illustrate the breakdown of Egypt’s political life since the presidential election two years ago.

headline.main: Candidate for President in Egypt Tempers His Expectations
headline.print_headline: Candidate for President in Egypt Tempers His Expectations
